&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WORCESTERSHIRE ACUTE HOSPITALS NHS TRUST&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;DEPARTMENT OF PAEDIATRICS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;BASED AT THE WORCESTERSHIRE ROYAL HOSPITAL&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;TRUST CLINICAL FELLOW IN PAEDIATRICS (ST3+ EQUIVALENT)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;£32,478 - £51,069&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Fixed Term Post for 12 months &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a middle grade post at the equivalent of ST3 level or above. The post holder will work with other middle grade paediatric doctors to provide continuous emergency cover for the Delivery Suite and the Level Two Neonatal Unit, Emergency Department and the 35 bedded Children’s Ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is suitable for a doctor who is working towards MRCPCH part II. This post has a 1 in 8 on-call rota at middle grade level.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interested candidates must have experience of working in Paediatrics for at least 2 years, including 6 months of neonatal intensive care and 6 months equivalent to that required at ST2 level in Paediatrics in an approved training post. Candidates should hold, or be eligible for full GMC registration together with a Licence to Practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquiries are welcome – please contact Dr &lt;strong&gt;Baylon Kamalarajan on 01905 760736&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
